Proposal: Node‑Based Visual Designer for FastLED LED Matrix Systems

🎯 Core Vision
A modular, node‑based environment where creators visually design LED patterns, audio‑reactive effects, transitions, and hardware interactions.  
The system compiles the node graph into optimized FastLED/Arduino‑style C++ code and deploys it to microcontrollers such as the ESP32‑S3.

The environment includes:

- Real‑time LED matrix preview  
- Node graph editor  
- Board manager (Arduino‑style)  
- Library manager (Arduino‑style)  
- Custom node creation  
- Multi‑pattern master node for sequencing, transitions, and hardware control  
- Audio input + FFT analysis nodes  
- Export-to‑microcontroller pipeline  

