🧠 2. Multi‑Pattern Master Node

This is the “brain” that represents the microcontroller.

Responsibilities:
- Holds all patterns  
- Manages transitions  
- Handles hardware inputs  
- Controls brightness  
- Schedules pattern switching  
- Manages audio input routing  
- Compiles everything into a single firmware file  

Features:
- Pattern Queue  
- Transition Node Support  
- Audio‑Driven Pattern Switching  
- Time‑Based Pattern Switching  
- GPIO‑Driven Pattern Switching  
- Global Palette Control  

