🧰 5. Arduino‑Style Board Manager

Allows adding new microcontroller targets as “Board Nodes”.

Board Node Properties:
- CPU type (ESP32‑S3, ESP32‑C3, RP2040, etc.)  
- Flash size  
- Available GPIO  
- I2S capabilities  
- Max LED count  
- Power constraints  
- Upload method (USB, OTA)  

Users can install new board definitions from a registry.

---

📚 6. Arduino‑Style Library Manager

Allows adding new node packs:

- New pattern nodes  
- New math nodes  
- New audio analysis nodes  
- New hardware nodes  
- New transitions  
- New color palettes  
- New matrix mapping utilities  

Supports community‑made node packs.

---

🧪 7. Custom Node Creation

Users can create nodes using:

- Visual scripting  
- Inline C++ snippets  
- GLSL‑style pixel expressions  
- Python‑style pseudo‑code that compiles to C++  

Custom nodes can be exported as shareable packages.

---

🛠️ 8. Code Generation Pipeline

The system compiles the node graph into:

- FastLED setup code  
- Pattern classes  
- Audio analysis classes  
- Transition classes  
- Hardware input handlers  
- Main loop with dt, frame timing, and FastLED.show()  

The output is a single .ino or .cpp project ready for upload.

---

🚀 9. Deployment Workflow

1. User builds node graph  
2. Live preview updates in real time  
3. User selects board (ESP32‑S3 etc.)  
4. System validates GPIO assignments  
5. System generates firmware  
6. User uploads via USB or OTA  
7. Microcontroller runs the compiled node graph  

